page.title: 19Bird Life around Stonegate
page.content: When I went on a walk on some of the footpaths in Stonegate I saw kestrel, woodpigeon,yellowhammer,magpie,carrion crow,blackbird,pheasant,skylark, sparrow and starling. In the school playground and the churchyard,house sparrows,blue tits, pied wagtails,chaffinches and robins can be seen.Flycatchers fly from gravestone to gravestone,catching insects.There is a rookery in the oak trees.Swallows and house martins fly around,nesting on the houses in the village. A little owl has been seen perched on a telegraph pole opposite the cricket field.A goldcrest has been seen in a local wood,and about 50 lapwings were seen circling over a field.
